    "narrative": "For LawDog today, **Lawrence Butler** stands out as the premier play at a 73.43 efficiency score. His matchup against Wacha is highly favorable, bolstered by a 15% skill-based projection boost and a 10% park factor advantage that outweighs his bottom-of-the-order placement. Similarly, **Daulton Varsho** earns a \"Strong\" start with a 70.72 rating; his ability to capitalize on a 4.55 xERA arm like Bello, combined with a 13% SP skill-matchup bump, makes him an essential fixture in the utility slot today. **Cal Raleigh** and **Jonathan Aranda** also anchor our offensive floor, both crossing the 67-point threshold as they look to exploit mid-rotation starters Bradley and Williams, respectively.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the morning involved **Masyn Winn**, who landed just shy of our 40.00 \"Zebras\" floor with a 39.21 score. While his base projection remains steady, the 19% downgrade due to the strength of Chandler\u2019s peripherals forced his benching to preserve our limited game caps. We are maintaining a strict threshold to avoid burning rosters spots on suboptimal matchups. We are closely monitoring the status of **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez**, both of whom were suppressed by the sub-3.00 xERA of Ritchie, effectively nullifying any value they might have provided had they faced a softer arm. With the rest of our core\u2014including **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**\u2014cleared for action, we are well-positioned for a productive day, provided **Geraldo Perdomo** can utilize his speed to navigate Sproat\u2019s delivery and overcome a slightly stagnant 58.54 projected output.",
